# =============================================================================
# fw_env.config — RK3588 A/B-virt emulator: U-Boot env access map (PWU-AB-2/AB-4)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# /etc/fw_env.config tells fw_setenv/fw_printenv (libubootenv, u-boot-tools)
# WHERE the U-Boot environment blob lives so the guest userspace can read AND
# write the SAME env the bootloader consults (BOOT_ORDER, BOOT_<bootname>_LEFT,
# upgrade_available, bootcount). Installed into BOTH slot rootfs images by a
# build_image.sh overlay. SHARED dependency of PWU-AB-2 (RAUC slot arm) and
# PWU-AB-4 (agent arm + healthy-marker) — see PWU_AB_2_RAUC_VERITY.md §4.5 and
# PWU_AB_4_APPLY_PORT.md §3.
#
# Format (one env copy per line; two lines = redundant A/B env):
#   <device>  <offset>  <env-size>  [<sector-size>  [<#blocks>]]
#
# !!! UNVERIFIED (§11.4.6) — THE LOAD-BEARING GATING DEPENDENCY !!!
#   The device/offset/size below MUST match the built u-boot.bin's CONFIG_ENV_*
#   storage EXACTLY. A mismatch = the guest writes an env the bootloader never
#   reads = a silent §11.4.108 SOURCE->RUNTIME gap. The conductor MUST, BEFORE
#   trusting any rauc install / fw_setenv slot arm, read the env storage config
#   from the built u-boot.bin and round-trip-verify: set a var in U-Boot at the
#   => prompt -> read it with fw_printenv in the guest, and vice-versa. Only when
#   that round-trip matches is this file trusted. Until then ab_rauc_verity.sh's
#   fw_setenv calls are EXPECTED to fail (the RED baseline) — honest, not a bug.
#
#   The qemu_arm64 U-Boot defconfig commonly uses CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_FAT (the env
#   is a FILE `uboot.env` on the FAT boot partition), which the classic raw
#   <device> <offset> <size> form below does NOT directly address. Two paths:
#     (A) If the built U-Boot is ENV_IS_IN_FAT: libubootenv >= recent supports a
#         FAT-file env entry; OR the persistent-env work (PWU_AB_4 §3) rebuilds
#         U-Boot with a RAW env region and this raw form is then correct.
#     (B) If a RAW env region is wired on the boot device, use the raw line.
#   Pick the path that matches the built artifact; do NOT assume. See the §8
#   Negative finding in PWU_AB_2_RAUC_VERITY.md.
#
# Sources verified 2026-06-11:
#   https://docs.u-boot.org/en/latest/develop/environment.html (fw_env.config
#     format: device, offset, env-size, sector-size)
#   https://rauc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/integration.html (RAUC needs
#     /etc/fw_env.config for its U-Boot backend)
# =============================================================================

# CANDIDATE RAW form (path B above) — a single env copy at a fixed offset on the
# boot device. ENABLE + CORRECT these numbers ONLY after reading the built
# u-boot.bin CONFIG_ENV_* and round-trip-verifying (see the UNVERIFIED note).
# The 0x4000 (16 KiB) env size + 0x200 (512 B) sector size are the libubootenv
# defaults, NOT yet confirmed against this U-Boot — placeholders, commented out.
#
#   <device>   <offset>   <env-size>  <sector-size>
# /dev/vda1    0x000000   0x4000      0x200

# NOTE: this file ships with the raw line COMMENTED so an un-round-trip-verified
# offset can never silently misdirect fw_setenv. Uncomment + correct it (or
# switch to the FAT-file form) in the bundle-build PWU after verification.
